unit.name: 53 (Welsh) Div HQ
unit.History: The 53rd Division served at Gallipolli and in Palestine during WWI, and was deactivated in 1918. In 1939, the division was reactivated as a First Line Territorial Division. After a brief spell as a Mixed Division it was reorganized as an Infantry Division in 1943. The division landed in Normandy on June 27th, and served in France, Belgium and the Netherlands. After the start of the German offensive on December 16th, the division was rushed to Belgium again, and positioned west of the river Meuse to prevent a German breakthrough.

commander.Name: R.K. Ross
commander.PersBio: Born in 1893, Ross commanded the 2nd Bn, The Queen's Royal Regiment in 1939. In 1940 he became commander of the 160th Brigade, and in September 1942 he took over the 53rd (Welsh) Division, a division which he led till the end of the war in Europe.
